<item>
            <title>[LU-9289] Fix fileset string length issue</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9289</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/21857&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/21857&lt;/a&gt; added this code in nodemap_fileset_seq_write():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;	OBD_ALLOC(nm_fileset, count);
	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (nm_fileset == NULL)
		RETURN(-ENOMEM);

	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (copy_from_user(nm_fileset, buffer, count))
		GOTO(out, rc = -EFAULT);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;count&apos; is the length of the string to write. So it is necessary to allocate count+1 for nm_fileset in order to add a &apos;\0&apos; after copy_from_user().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
